      "related_files": [
        "goseg/uploadsvc/adapters/upload_payload.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/service.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/adapters/upload_payload_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Adapter rejects reset payload extras (`Endpoint`, `Remote`, `Fix`, `SelectedDrive`) in `upload_payload.go` with a hard-coded error.",
        "Service execute path independently enforces nil/mutual-exclusion checks for reset vs open-endpoint request payloads in `newUploadDispatcher` descriptors.",
        "Tests assert both parsing and service-level execution constraints separately, suggesting repeated ownership of the same invariants."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a single command-construction/validation stage shared by adapter and executor (e.g., a `uploadsvc.ValidateCommand` used before dispatch) so transport parsing stays thin and action invariants live in one module.",
